
1. What is data cleaning and why is it important in Streamlit apps?

Data cleaning fixes messy data (missing values, duplicates, wrong formats) before analysis/visualization. Critical for Streamlit because dirty data = broken charts + wrong insights in interactive apps.

Real Impact:

Raw data → 30% missing → Charts fail ❌
Clean data → 100% complete → Perfect dashboard ✅



2. How do you handle missing values while cleaning data?

Pandas methods in Streamlit:

python
# Check missing
st.write(df.isnull().sum())

# Drop rows with missing
df_clean = df.dropna()

# Fill with average
df['age'].fillna(df['age'].mean(), inplace=True)

# Forward fill
df.fillna(method='ffill', inplace=True)



3. What is the difference between dropna() and fillna()?

| Method   | Action                       | When to Use                      |
| -------- | ---------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| dropna() | Delete rows/columns with NaN | Few missing values (<5%)         |
| fillna() | Replace NaN with value       | Most data is good, preserve rows |

python
# Drop all rows with ANY missing
df.dropna(inplace=True)

# Fill only specific column
df['salary'].fillna(50000, inplace=True)



4. How do you remove duplicate rows in a dataset?

python
# Remove exact duplicates
df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)

# Remove duplicates based on specific columns
df.drop_duplicates(subset=['email'], inplace=True)

# Streamlit example
if st.button("Remove Duplicates"):
    df = df.drop_duplicates()
    st.success(f"Removed {len(df_original) - len(df)} duplicates")

